@node introduction "Why the #$%#!!! write this?"
@{jcenter}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@{jleft}	Recently, I've been gifted a subscription to Science News, and have since had
the pleasure of reading some truly facsinating stuff cover to cover on a regular basis.
One of the common themes is the Keppler telescopes unrelenting search for planets, and
how many of them this thing has found. So I went to NASA's site, and downloaded a
@{"CSV file" link "files/ExoplanetArchive.csv/MAIN"} containing all the exoplanets known in 2011. When I fired up the file in
Ubuntu, LibreOffice displayed it. Which is fine, I guess, but when you have a simple
netbook with an Intel Atom running it, even with Ubuntu, it takes awhile. The trusty 'ol
Amiga didn't fare much better, as I don't have much in the way of spreadsheets. Though I
do have one, which is written in German. And I took Spanish in high school.. <sigh> (I
think there's an English version available, but I wasn't about to go digging for it.)
	So, remembering my tinkerings with MUI and NList, I figured it should be easy
to whip up a program that parses and dumps CSV data into a multi-column list.
Unfortunately, this required hook functions. Fortunately, Jens Langner (according to
the .h file) came up with a hook function header which made life a hell of alot
easier. (SDI_hook.h, @{"http://www.sf.net/projects/sditools" system "c:openurl http://www.sf.net/projects/sditools/"}) So this enabled me to write
a really simple CSV file viewer, that allows for default tool references from a
project icon, as well as drag & drop functionality. Unfortunately, MUI makes things
incredibly easy, and I started adding other features to it. I figured I'd upload it
now, before it sufferes from too much bloating because of that.
	And now, I have a CSV file viewer (which still has a few @{"bugs" link bugs} in it), with an
AREXX port for automating stuff (like re-arranging YAM's CSV export into something 
ThunderBird or GMail can read and vice-versa), with a def_csv.info icon set up so I
don't have to mess with it.
@{jcenter}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}
@endnode

@node requirements "What you need to run it."
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{b}Requirements@{ub}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@{jleft}	An Amiga ;) (Or UAE/Fellow/Whatever emulator you prefer, allowing for H/W)
	
	68020+ with WorkBench 3.0 (Probably will work with 2.x, but I've not tested this)
	
	2MB RAM should be fine (Only tested under A1200's, which have 2MB Chip anyway)
	
	MUI
	
	NList MUI class
	
	BetterString MUI class
	
	Some CSV files (I've included a couple)
	
	Something that would benefit from one of your CSV files, and has an @{"Arexx" link arexx} port. :D
	
@{jcenter}@{b}Recommended:@{ub}
@{jleft}
	OpenURL.library (For visiting websites from the @{"Entry info" link "images/row_info.iff/MAIN"} window)
	
	codesets.library (For loading/saving unicode files)
	
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{b}Requirements@{ub}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@endnode

@node usage "What does this button do? ... BOOM!!! oops..."
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{b}Usage@{ub}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@{jleft}	Pretty easy to use. You can launch it directly via its tool icon, or through
the @{"project icon" link "images/icon_info.iff/MAIN"} of a CSV file (notice the Default Tool and @{b}Stacksize@{ub} settings). Then
the @{"Main window" link "images/main_window.iff/MAIN"} pops up, with your file loaded, or with nothing, depending on how it
was launched. The filename, if any, is shown at the top, next to the file button (which
pops up a file requester for whatever you want to load ;).
	If you have a unicode encoded (UTF-8, windows-1250, etc..) CSV file, and
codesets.library installed, the cycle gadget next to the load and save icons can
select which encoding to import. This can also be disabled in the @{"settings" link "images/settings_export.iff/MAIN"} window.
The drawer and disk icons can be used to load and export (CSV) files instead of
the pull-down menus, too.
	Double clicking on an list entry opens the @{"Entry window" link "images/row_info.iff/MAIN"}, which lists the single
row in a more pleasing (sometimes) format. You can save this as a text file with the
file gadget below the list. Also, double-clicking a url in this window will send it to
your browser, assuming you have OpenUrl.library installed. The @{"Column tab" link "images/column_info.iff/MAIN"} just lists
all entries in a single column, and can similarly be saved with that page's file gadget.
The cycle gadget just cycles through the various columns.
	Also, I added a search gadget. As this was a bit of an afterthought, its only a
case-sensative search using c's strstr command. It'll search through the file, highlight
any row with the matching text, and display which column it's in. 
	The titlebar will sort the list by whichever column's title you click on.
@{jcenter}@{U}@{b}CAUTION!!@{UB}@{UU}
@{b}This uses a bubble sort method, and can be @{i}very@{ui} slow!@{ub}
@{jleft}
	Next to the search gadget is the equally new filter gadget, which will limit
the display to only rows containing a matching string in the search box.
	There are also some menus:
	Project
		@{b}Open@{ub} - Opens an ASL requester for a new file.
		@{i}Export@{ui}
			@{b}HTML@{ub} - Exports to HTML using export @{"preferences" link "images/settings_export.iff/MAIN"}
			@{b}CSV@{ub} - Exports to CSV using export @{"preferences" link "images/settings_export.iff/MAIN"}
		@{"About ViewCSV" link "images/about_viewcsv.iff/MAIN"} - The obligitory brag window. Also contains an @{"AREXX" link "images/arexx_info.iff/MAIN"} tab,
			for looking up commands when you're too lazy to dig up this
			AmigaGuide ;).
		@{b}About MUI@{ub} - The MUI about window, as requested for all MUI apps.
		@{b}Quit@{ub} - Hmm. I can't remember what this does..... ;)
	List	
		@{"File Info" link "images/file_info.iff/MAIN"} - Some information about the loaded file.
		@{"Entry Info" link "images/row_info.iff/MAIN"} - Same window that pops up after double clicking a list entry.
		@{b}Reset@{ub} - restores display to original file, despite filtering/sorting.
	Settings
		@{"Preferences" link "images/settings_display.iff/MAIN"} - Opens the @{"settings" link "settings"} window.

	That should cover it, it @{b}is@{ub} a pretty basic (actually, C ;) program after all.

@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{b}Usage@{ub}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@endnode

@node arexx "More excuses to play with a text editor!"
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{b}AREXX@{ub}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
Aside from the usual MUI commands, I've added a few as well.
@{jleft}
@{b}getfield@{ub} @{u}row column @{uu} Retrieves field at @{u}row@{uu}, @{u}column@{uu}.
@{b}getinfo@{ub} @{u}option@{uu} Gets information on @{u}option@{uu}.
	@{b}option@{ub} can be:
		@{u}rows@{uu} # of rows in file.
		@{u}cols@{uu} # of columns in file.
		@{u}filename@{uu} Path/name of file.
		@{u}size@{uu} size of file in bytes.
		@{u}titlerow@{uu} The title row for the file.
		@{u}fields@{uu} # of entries in the file.
@{b}getrow@{ub} @{u}row #@{uu} Get the entire row.
@{b}getcol@{ub} @{u}col #@{uu} Get the entire column.
@{b}sort@{ub}	@{u}column #@{uu} Sort the list by column.
@{b}resetlist@{ub}	Resets the list order and filtering.
@{b}listfile@{ub}	@{u}option@{uu} @{u}filename@{uu} Various file operations to filename.
	@{b}Options@{ub} can be:
		@{u}Load@{uu} loads @{u}filename@{uu}.
		@{u}savehtml@{uu} Exports csv data to html @{u}filename@{uu}.
		@{u}savecsv@{uu} Exports CSV file to @{u}filename@{uu}.
		@{u}saveentry@{uu} Save current entry to @{u}filename@{uu}.
		@{u}savelist@{uu} Save current column to @{u}filename@{uu}.
@{b}select@{ub}	@{u}option@{uu} @{u}value@{uu} Select row or column
	@{b}Option@{ub} can be:
		@{u}row@{uu} select row #value.
		@{u}col@{uu} Select columns #value.

@{b}filter@{ub}	@{u}string@{uu} Filters all entries containing @{u}string@{uu}.
@{b}search@{ub}	@{u}string@{uu} Searches for @{u}string@{uu}.

	All these commands put their data into RESULT (needs "options results" in the
script). Also, the @{"About ViewCSV" link "images/arexx_info.iff/MAIN"} window has a list of these commands. (A pretty
accurate one, as I'm too lazy to type it twice and just dumped the source to the
clipboard for this guide ;).

@{jleft}@{b}
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{b}AREXX@{ub}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@endnode

@node history "History, and to-do."
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{b}History@{ub}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@{B}@{U}History@{UU}@{UB}
@{jleft} @{u}ViewCSV 1.0@{uu}
	* First release
 @{u}ViewCSV 1.1@{uu}
	* Fixed weird international character bug, caused by signed characters.
	  (©,ř,ć,ĺ,etc.. are all >127 in ascii, and get "rolled over" to negative
	  values when typcast as a signed char, which I used a <=1 statement to
	  allocate fields when parsing)
	* Added error trapping for memory allocations (oops...)
	* Fixed "uneven" csv files (ones with an irregular number of columns per
	  line). Now *** BLANK *** shows up when that happens (this will be
	  customizable in the future).
 @{u}ViewCSV 1.2@{uu}
 	* Fixed 64K gas-gauge bug
 	* Added percent readouts to gas-gauge
 @{u}ViewCSV 1.3@{uu}
 	* Added URL recognition via OpenURL.library
 	* Removed "escape characters" from the display
 	* Fixed column sort crash
 	* Added search and filter options.
 	* Added unicode support via codesets.library
 	* "Ghosting" of nlist displays for faster updates
	  
@{jcenter}@{B}@{U}Future@{UU}@{UB}
@{jleft} 	* More menus. (Load menu, AREXX macro menu, etc..)
	* Preferences window
 	  @{i}Customize separate, newline, and escape characters.@{ui} @{b}DONE!@{ub}
 	  Customize CSV file title.
	* Tootypes support
 	  Everything in the Prefs window set this way.
	* Port to AROS, OS4, possibly MorphOS.
	* @{i}Email address and URL recognition.@{ui} @{b}DONE!@{ub}
	* Fix @{"Bugs" link bugs}

@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{b}Future@{ub}@{"Contact" link contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{"Settings" link settings}
@endnode

