@node settings "But I don't want a grey background!"
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link Contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{b}Settings@{ub}
@{jleft}	The settings menu has a preferences option, which amazingly, opens the
preferences @{"window" link "images/settings_display.iff/MAIN"}. This window defaults to the "display" tab, which lists some
general options.
	The Separator, Escape, and New Row cycle gadgets change the characters
marking those attributes. You would, for example, change the Separator gadget
to TAB if you wanted to import a .tsv file. If you have a weird file, you can
use custom characters, which will "unghost" the text gadget below the cycle.
	The "Blank Entry" gadget allows you to change the default field for
empty fields. These are usually blank fields, or fields beyond the end of
the file (If you have a file with 10 columns, and the last row only has 3,
7 of them will contain this).
	If you have codesets.library installed, the "Unicode Support"
checkbox will appear, with which you can en/disable support for different
charsets. If codesets.library isn't installed, this doesn't even show up.

	The @{"Export" link "images/settings_export.iff/MAIN"} tab shows the various export options (strangly enough :).
The CSV side allows you to change the Separator, Escape, and New Row attributes,
for when you export a CSV file (You can export a TSV for Semi-colon delineated
file, for example).

	The "Export Escapes" checkbox will en/dis-able escape codes being exported.

	The HTML side has the ability to change various colors for HTML export.
This @{b}does not@{ub} work with the included html export AREXX script. The icons on top allow
you to load and save the color settings to a file, and the "Default" check will load
the last settings when the program starts again.
	Again, codeset options are available with codesets.library installed, and
setting this cycle gadget determines which codeset to use when exporting a file.
	
@{jcenter}@{"Introduction" link introduction}@{"Requirements" link requirements}@{"Usage" link usage}@{"AREXX" link arexx}@{"History" link history}@{"Contact" link Contact}@{"Bugs" link bugs}@{b}Settings@{ub}
@endnode